xcess of vapor and heat form its industrial operations by lawrence iliff wall street journal may nd  national oil company petróleos mexicanos created a cogeneration unit for electricity production during a meeting of its board of directors friday and shuffled executives at its restructured exploration and production unit the company said the new pemex cogeneration and services division will oversee the harnessing of excess vapor and heat from the oil firm’s industrial operations—especially at refineries—to produce electricity for sale an energy overhaul last year ended pemex’s monopoly on oil production while also opening up the electricity sector which has been dominated by the state utility comision federal de electricidad in wake of the reform pemex plans to go from being the nation’s biggest electricity consumer to becoming a net producer the company has said the pemex board named eleazar gomez zapata as director of the cogeneration unit he previously served as the maintenance coordinator at the corporate operations unit the oil company’s board also voted to restructure its exploration and production unit as the company prepares to compete with private players rather than having one director named by the nation’s president as was standard practice for decades pemex will now have a threeperson committee to divide up those duties with the executives named by the board former exploration and production chief gustavo hernandez was named operations director of the committee juan javier hinojosa was named production director and jose antonio escalera will be the exploration chief pemex said in a news release tags electricity production mexico mexico energy reform oil production pemex   ut main    ut directory    ut direct    canvas    privacy policy    accessibility  jackson school of geosciences the university of texas at austin site last modified april   pemexs board of directors approved the start of operations of the productive stateowned subsidiaries ep and cogen